This paper is about machine learning algorithms for word sense disambiguation, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of lexical features, which is a common approach in machine learning (ML) for natural language processing (NLP), so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of classifiers and training text, which are common in information retrieval (IR) and cybernetics (CY), respectively, so cs.IR and cs.CY are also possible sub-categories.
